# ══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
# AI Proxy v4.0 — Configuration
# Copy this file to .env and fill in your values.
# You need at least ONE provider configured to start the proxy.
# ══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════

# ── Anthropic (Claude models) ──────────────────────────────────────────────────
# Get your key at https://platform.claude.com
# IMPORTANT: Add credits at https://platform.claude.com under Billing.
# Without credits you will get a "Your credit balance is too low" error.
# ANTHROPIC_API_KEY=sk-ant-xxxxxxxxxxxxxxxx

# ── OpenAI (GPT models) ────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# Get your key at https://platform.openai.com
# When set, gpt-* model requests route directly to OpenAI.
# OPENAI_API_KEY=sk-xxxxxxxxxxxxxxxx

# ── Google Gemini ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# Get your key at https://aistudio.google.com
# When set, gemini-* model requests route to Google Gemini.
# GEMINI_API_KEY=AIzaxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxx

# ── Ollama (free local models — no API key needed) ────────────────────────────
# Install Ollama from https://ollama.com — completely free, runs on your machine.
# Set OLLAMA_BASE_URL to enable it, then list which models you have pulled.
#
# To pull a model:   ollama pull llama3
# Available models:  llama3, mistral, codellama, phi3, qwen2, deepseek-r1, gemma3
#
# OLLAMA_BASE_URL=http://localhost:11434
# OLLAMA_MODELS=llama3,mistral,codellama

# ── OpenRouter (200+ models via one key) ──────────────────────────────────────
# Get your free key at https://openrouter.ai — BYOK, pay per token.
# Gives access to GPT-5, Claude, Llama 4, DeepSeek-R1, Mistral and more.
#
# When set, requests with "openrouter/" prefix route to OpenRouter.
# Unknown models (not claude-/gpt-/gemini-/ollama) also route here automatically.
#
# Usage: model="openrouter/meta-llama/llama-3-8b-instruct"
# Model list: https://openrouter.ai/models
#
# OPENROUTER_API_KEY=sk-or-xxxxxxxxxxxxxxxx
# OPENROUTER_SITE_URL=http://localhost:3030
# OPENROUTER_SITE_NAME=AI Proxy

# ── Fallback (auto-retry on failure) ─────────────────────────────────────────
# If the primary provider returns an error (429, 500, 502, 503, 529),
# the proxy automatically retries the next available provider in this list.
#
# Example: if Anthropic hits a rate limit, it falls back to OpenAI automatically.
# The order here sets the priority — first entry is tried first.
#
# Only enabled providers (with keys set above) are used.
# FALLBACK_ORDER=anthropic,openai,gemini,ollama,openrouter

# ── Model Aliases (silent model rewriting) ───────────────────────────────────
# Rewrite any model name before routing. Useful for directing "standard" model
# names to cheaper local equivalents without changing client code.
#
# Format: ALIAS_<from>=<to>
# Multiple aliases supported (add as many ALIAS_* lines as needed).
#
# ALIAS_gpt-4o=ollama/llama4
# ALIAS_gpt-4=openrouter/meta-llama/llama-3-70b-instruct

# ── Smart Routing (3-tier model selection) ───────────────────────────────────
# When enabled, the proxy analyzes each prompt and routes to the most
# cost-effective model tier automatically:
#
#   Tier 1 (fast/cheap) — simple tasks: summarize, translate, list, classify
#   Tier 2 (balanced)   — default: coding, writing, general questions
#   Tier 3 (powerful)   — complex: analyze, compare, deep research, long prompts
#
# The proxy overrides whatever model the client requested.
#
# SMART_ROUTING=true
# ROUTING_TIER1_MODEL=claude-haiku-4-5-20251001
# ROUTING_TIER2_MODEL=claude-sonnet-4-6
# ROUTING_TIER3_MODEL=claude-opus-4-6

# ── Daily Budget Caps (per provider) ─────────────────────────────────────────
# Set a USD spending limit per provider per day (resets at midnight).
# Requests are rejected with HTTP 429 once the limit is reached.
# Set to 0 (default) to disable.
#
# ANTHROPIC_DAILY_BUDGET_USD=0
# OPENAI_DAILY_BUDGET_USD=0
# GEMINI_DAILY_BUDGET_USD=0
# OPENROUTER_DAILY_BUDGET_USD=0

# ── Exact Prompt Cache ────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# Caches identical requests (same model + messages) in memory.
# Identical repeat requests return instantly at $0 cost.
# Cache resets on proxy restart.
#
# CACHE_ENABLED=true
# CACHE_MAX_SIZE=500

# ── Semantic Cache (requires @xenova/transformers) ────────────────────────────
# Matches semantically similar prompts using local sentence embeddings.
# "What is ML?" and "Explain machine learning" can return the same cached answer.
#
# Setup: npm install @xenova/transformers
# First start downloads ~23MB model (Xenova/all-MiniLM-L6-v2).
# Runs entirely in-process — no external server needed.
#
# SEMANTIC_CACHE=false
# SEMANTIC_THRESHOLD=0.92
# SEMANTIC_CACHE_MAX_SIZE=200

# ── PROXY_API_KEY — Password protection ───────────────────────────────────────
#
# What it does:
#   Adds a password layer so only people who know this key can use your proxy.
#   Anyone connecting must send this value as their API key in their tool.
#
# When to use it:
#   - Running on a server (deployed online)  → ALWAYS set this
#   - Sharing with teammates over a network  → ALWAYS set this
#   - Running locally for yourself only      → Safe to leave blank
#
# PROXY_API_KEY=

# ── CORS_ORIGIN — Browser access control ──────────────────────────────────────
#
# Controls which websites running in a browser can call your proxy.
#   * (default)                  → Allow any website (fine for local use)
#   https://myapp.com            → Only allow your specific app
#   http://localhost:5173        → Only allow a local frontend (e.g. Vite)
#
# Note: CLI tools (Claude Code, curl) are NOT affected by CORS.
# CORS_ORIGIN=*

# ── Other settings ────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

# Port (default 3030)
# PORT=3030

# Request timeout in milliseconds (default 120000 = 2 minutes)
# Increase for slow models or very long documents.
# REQUEST_TIMEOUT_MS=120000

# Rate limit per IP per minute (default 60, set to 0 to disable)
# Protects against abuse if PROXY_API_KEY is shared on a server.
# RATE_LIMIT_PER_MIN=60
